Navigate to other release versions of Doxee Platform Template Designer

[6.6](https://docs.doxee.com/docs/en/template-designer-6-6)

[6.7](https://docs.doxee.com/docs/en/template-designer-6-7)

The *Doxee Template Designer *built-in spell check is based on word lists. The individual words are stored in a sequential file and are separated by a line feed (carriage return).

## Utilisation
The option for the spell check can be found in the context menu via *Outline view*. Individual blocks can be checked as well as the entire *Page Sequence*.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

*Figure 161. usage of the spell check*

In the upcoming dialog, all false terms are highlighted in red and you have to decide in each case, whether to ignore this term or to be added to the user dictionary.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

*Figure 162. execution of the spell check*

Alternatively, you can also replace the term by one of the suggestions. Just click below on a suggestion and select Change to change only that word or Change All to change all occurrences of the word.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

*Figure 163. replace term by a suggestion*

## Allocation of the language in the document
In order for the spell check working correctly, a corresponding language code must be assigned to the text.

The appropriate language option (group *Hyphenation*) is located under *Properties &gt; Advanced*.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

*Figure 164. corresponding langauge code to the text*

The language can be used on the Page Sequence, as well as on block-level. If the document is written in one language, a sole assignment of the attribute language on the *Page Sequence *suffices. Differing blocks can be overwritten by assigning a different value.

## Configuration
The configuration is done via the menu *Edit &gt; Preferences &gt; Infinica / Spelling.*

*![](data:image/png;base64,)*

*Figure 165. Configuration of the spelling*

With the *Add *button you can add new word lists - with *Edit *and *Remove *accordingly modify

or remove. Using the function *Import *and *Export*, lists are stored externally or loaded from an external source.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

*Figure 166. add new word list*

First, under Language the desired language code is entered. Then you can link one or more word lists with this language code.
